I am beyond proud and excited to announce that @jason.tyler.k and I have just signed the lease for a new attraction in downtown Salem Massachusetts. After many years of trying to make this happen, The Salem Museum of Torture will open its doors this fall to satisfy the growing morbid curiosity that swirls around our beautiful witch city. 
Wander through the dimly lit chambers of our museum at your own pace and learn the startling truths of history’s most cruel and unusual punishments. Featuring life size displays, recreations and authentic instruments of torture, this bloodcurdling exhibit is sure to leave you astonished at the cruelty of the human condition. 

Please follow our new Instagram page for updates and sneak peeks, see you soon! 

https://www.instagram.com/salemmuseumoftorture/

#salemmassachusetts #torture #darkhistory #museum #medieval #attraction #witchcity

Cannot believe I got the chance to meet Amelia Kinkade. I vividly remember being a kid at my local video store and being mesmerized by the Night of the Demons 2 standee. Thank you so much Salem Horror Fest!

Opening announcements coming soon! @salemmuseumoftorture 

Hark! 'tis the dungeon's groan I hear;
And lo, a squalid band appear, 
with sallow cheek, and hollow eye!
Unwilling, lo, the neck they bend;
Yet, through thy pow'r, their terrors end, 
And with their heads the sorrows fly.

SPECIAL ANNOUNCEMENT! The Salem Museum of Torture officially opens it’s dungeon doors on August 26th! Tickets are reservation only and will go on sale through our website on August 1st. Limited tickets available, so mark your calendar and book before they’re all gone. See you soon! Www.SalemTorture.com

Had the absolute pleasure of visiting the Salem Night Faire this past weekend and it was the highlight of our season. An incredibly atmospheric, ethereal experience that felt like we had stepped into a nightmarish A24 film. Filled to the brim with beyond talented vendors, actors, artists, and a host of haunting creatures, this was an experience we can’t wait to do again next year. Bravo everyone involved, you knocked this out of the park! 🖤💀

A massive Thank You to everyone who came out to support us in our first year. We had an incredibly successful season and it wouldn’t be possible without all of you. The future is bright and we’ll just be getting bigger and better!
We will remain open for most of November before we close for our winter break for renovations and additions. Hope you all had a happy and healthy Halloween Season, and from the bottom of our hearts, we appreciate every one of you. See you again soon! 🎃
